===Etymology===
From Middle English {{term|behemoth|behemoth, bemoth|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|LL.|en}}, from {{etyl|he|en}} {{term|בהמות|tr=bəhēmōth|lang=he}}. The Hebrew word is either:
* an intensive plural of {{term|בהמה||tr=bəhēmāh|beast|lang=he}}, from {{etyl|sem-pro|en}} (compare Ethiopic {{term|||tr=bəhma|dumb, speechless|lang=gez}}, Arabic {{term|||tr=ʼabham|animal|lang=ar}} (declined as ''bahma(t)'', ''bahīma(t)'')), or
* a borrowing of {{etyl|egy|en}} {{term|||tr=p-ehe-mau|hippopotamus|lit=water-ox|lang=egy}}.

